OL,3,CGovernment's plans to boost workers'
OL,4,Crights to be unveiled
OL,6,FSome measures, such as the right to
OL,7,F"switch off" at the end of a working
OL,8,Fday, are not in the Bill but will be
OL,9,Fincluded in a so-called Next Steps
OL,10,Fdocument for further consideration and
OL,11,Fconsultation.
OL,13,FUnder the Bill, the existing two-year
OL,14,Fqualifying period for protections from
OL,15,Funfair dismissal will be removed and
OL,16,Fworkers will have the right from the
OL,17,Ffirst day in a job.
OL,19,FMinisters say this will benefit nine
OL,20,Fmillion workers who have been with
OL,21,Ftheir employer for less than two years.
