OL,6,FAround 30,000 fathers or partners will
OL,7,Fbe eligible for paternity leave, while
OL,8,Fan extra 1.5 million parents will have
OL,9,Fthe right to unpaid leave from day one.
OL,11,FFlexible working will be made the
OL,12,Fdefault position "where practical",
OL,13,Fwhile large employers will be required
OL,14,Fto create action plans on addressing
OL,15,Fany gender pay gaps.
OL,17,FOn the controversial issue of zero-
OL,18,Fhours contracts, employers will have
OL,19,Fto offer a guaranteed hours contract
OL,20,Fbased on a 12-week reference period.
